Package: pressR
Title: Pressure Distribution Analysis for Capacitive Sensor Systems
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Raban", "Heller", email = "raban.heller@charite.de",
    role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-8006-9742"))
Description: Parse, analyze, and visualize pressure distribution data from
    capacitive sensor systems including novel emed, pedar, and pliance
    platforms. Provides predefined sensor coordinate layouts for in-shoe
    pressure measurement, saddle pressure mapping (equine and bicycle),
    seating assessment, and barefoot pedography. Includes functions for
    peak pressure, center of pressure, pressure-time integrals, regional
    analysis with anatomical masks, symmetry indices, and gait cycle
    detection. Ships with an interactive Shiny application for data
    exploration and report generation.
